{"id":3076,"date":"2012-04-28T10:52:00","date_gmt":"2012-04-28T14:52:00","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=3076"},"modified":"2019-05-20T10:25:36","modified_gmt":"2019-05-20T06:25:36","slug":"salat-description-adhan","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/04\/28\/salat-description-adhan\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Adhan: Description of call to prayer, its wording"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Mahdhurah reported: The Prophet of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, taught the call to prayer like this, \u201cAllah is the greatest. Allah is greatest. I bear witness there is no God but Allah. I bear witness there is no God but Allah. I bear witness Muhammad is the Messenger of Allah. I bear witness Muhammad is the Messenger of Allah.\u201d Then, it is repeated, saying, \u201cI bear witness there is no God but Allah. I bear witness there is no God but Allah. I bear witness Muhammad is the Messenger of Allah. I bear witness Muhammad is the Messenger of Allah. Come to prayer, twice. Come to success, twice.\u201d Ishaq added, \u201cAllah is the greatest. Allah is the greatest. There is no God but Allah.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 379<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em><strong>Sahih\u00a0<\/strong><\/em>(authentic) according to Muslim<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0645\u064e\u062d\u0652\u0630\u064f\u0648\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0646\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0651 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0647\u064e\u0630\u064e\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0630\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u